A Sidon set is a set of numbers such that all pairwise sums are distinct. 

To prove the upper bound of 3/5, we need to show that if `c ≥ 3/5`, then there exists a finite set `A` such that all 4-element subsets of `A` have difference sets of size 11, but any Sidon subset `S` of `A` satisfies `|S| < c * |A|`.

